Patch Set 6: Code-Review-1

Thanks Abhishek!

Code etc all looks good.

A minor comment on docs.

There are various keepalive options on a system (TCP etc).

I think it would be useful to make it clear to operators that this changes the HTTP level keepalive (http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/HTTP_persistent_connection) behaviour.

I know there are other similar changes for other projects so it may be too late, but changing wsgi_keep_alive to http_keepalive would be a bit clearer I think.

If it is too late to change that, then it's probably worth mentioning that the option controls the HTTP keep-alive, and that when set to True the server will return the header 'Connection: close', and when False the server will return 'Connection: Keep-Alive' in its responses.
